VA has enacted Pharmacy Disaster Relief Plan for central Florida. Veterans needing an emergency supply of medications can go to any retail pharmacy open to the public, with a written Rx or active VA prescription bottle, that is not older than six months and has active refills.
For information about compensation or pension benefits checks, please call the toll-free number 1-800-827-1000. The phone line is operational Monday -Friday 8 a.m. to 9 p.m. EST. #HurricaneDorian

Veterans or their families should call 1-800-507-4571 to receive information on where to go for care, how to receive prescription drugs, or any other concerns they may have about their care. The phone line will be open 24 hours a day, seven days a week. #HurricaneDorian
The emergency department is scheduled to remain open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, throughout the storm period. Please note the VA is not a shelter. #HurricaneDorian

Due to #HurricaneDorian, the Orlando VA Healthcare System is cancelling all scheduled appointments for its outpatient clinics in Lake Baldwin & Lake Nona. Veterans needing emergency medical services may visit the Lake Nona VA Medical Center Emergency Dept at 13800 Veterans Way.
